From:         "Aldon L. Nielsen" <anielsen@ISC.SJSU.EDU>
Subject:      Re: the shape of jazz to come/gone
In-Reply-To:  <199510290358.UAA23562@sparta.SJSU.EDU>
 
according to L.A. Times, Don Cherry died at age 58 a few days ago --
Anybody who saw him perform recently (the only trumpet player i know of
in jazz to play from a lotus position!) knows how energetic and inventive
Cherry continued to be in the years after departing from the Ornette
Coleman band -- Once read poems with him at D.C. space between his sets
at the piano and trumpet -- a beautiful musician and a great friend to
all who knew him --
