re:  Don Cherry's death.
Sacrilege no doubt on the day after the conclusion of the World Series;
preface too to a Stormy Monday after this first day of Day Light Savings,
but. . .
Cherry died of liver cancer, one might say of not having access to
the repacement parts available to the Mick.
 
Don Cherry, Ornette Coleman, Ed Blackwell, Charlie Hayden are
still on recordings and YET to be appreciated.  The character of that
"yet" is manifold--prospective but not Emersonian.
