NORTHERN TERRITORY
 
 
Darwin
 
4 November  FAW workshop: Wendy Hansen on the business of freelancing.
2-5pm Frog Hollow Arts Precinct, 56 McMinn Street Darwin.
 
25 November  Publish or be Damned!: The Bold and Beautiful approach to
Publishers. Tutor; editor Janet Blagg. Workshop covers: # How to set out
and present your manuscript, # Deciding who to send it to, # What you
should send, # Covering letter, # How to write a publishing proposal, #
Book publishing/manuscript editors. 2-5pm Frog Hollow Arts Precinct, 56
McMinn Street Darwin.
 
 
Alice Springs
 
Award winning Victorian writer Barry Hill will be conducting writers'
workshops at the YWCA in Alice Springs over the first two weekends of
November. The workshops are the last in a series Barry has conducted in
Alice this year during his stint as Literature Board sponsored Writer in
the Community.
 
Workshop 1, 4-5 November 1.30 - 5pm each day. Finding your voice. A
workshop designed both for those who have made a start in writing and those
who have not. The focus will be on autobiographical poetry and prose. Two
sessions composed of close reading, writing exercises and student
presentation of their work. Cost $5 per session.
 
Workshop 2, 11-12 November 1.30 - 5pm each day. Your Sacred Place and other
Cultures. A workshop on the task of finding/defining in your work/self that
which is of central importance. This project is tackled by reference to our
understanding of other cultures. The focus is on selected poetry and prose
in translation with two sessions composed of close reading, writing
exercises and the presentation of one's own work. Cost $5 per session.
 
 
For further information about any of these events contact Andrew McMillan,
Literature Officer, Northern Territory Community Writing Program GPO Box
1774 Darwin NT 0801, phone/fax (089) 412651.
 
 
 
 
 
