COMPETITIONS
 
 
 
24th NOVEMBER: SUTHERLAND SHIRE COUNCIL SHORT STORY COMPETITION
$500 in cash prizes to be won and stories published in Artbeat. Any topic,
1500-2000 words. Category A: Age 19 years and over 1st Prize $250, 2nd
Prize $100. Category B: Age 18 years and under 1st Prize $100, 2nd Prize
$50. Sutherland Shire Council and the sponsors reserve the right to publish
all or part of a particular story for up to 2 years. Council will not have
sole copyright of each entry and stories may therefore be published
elsewhere. Present your submission on A4 paper preferably typed, specifying
which category you are entering. Judges decision will be final and the
winners will be announced and printed in the December/January edition of
ARTbeat. Send entries to: Genevieve Antill, ARTbeat c/Sutherland
Entertainment Centre, Eton St, Sutherland NSW 2232.
 
30TH NOVEMBER NITA B KIBBLE LITERARY AWARD FOR WOMEN WRITERS
For a published book of fiction or nonfiction classifiable as "life
writing". Value of 1996 Award: $15,000. The work is to be of or in
connection with normal Australian life, written in English language and
have a minimum length of 50,000 words. For conditions and entry form:
Charitable Trusts Manager, Perpetual Trustees, 39 Hunter St Sydney NSW 2000
(02) 229 9866.
 
30TH NOVEMBER NITA MAY DOBBIE LITERARY AWARD FOR WOMEN WRITERS
Encouragement Award to Women Writers for a FIRST published book of fiction
or nonfiction classifiable as "life writing". Value of 1996 Award: $5,000.
This award is intended as encouragement prize to Australian Women writers
who have not yet achieved a professional reputation as writers. The award
is for an author's FIRST published book. The work is to be of or in
connection with normal Australian life, written in the English language and
have a minimum length of 50,000 words. For conditions and entry form:
Charitable Trusts Manager, Perpetual Trustees, 39 Hunter St Sydney NSW 2000
(02) 229 9866.
 
30 NOVEMBER EMMA DARCY AWARD
for unpublished romance manuscripts between 45,000 and100,000 words, first
prize $2,000.Guidelines and entry forms from 21 Violet Street Miranda NSW
2228.
 
30 NOVEMBER PAPYRUS PUBLISHING SEVENTH LITERARY COMPETITION
Minimum age 18. There are three categories - short stories (up to 3,000
words); open poetry and haiku with an Australian theme. First prize in each
category is $80. Second and third prizes is a Papyrus Publishing book
voucher. Details from Papyrus Publishing PO Box 144 Upper Fern Tree Gully
Victoria 3156. Phone (03) 9758 7395, fax (03) 9752 4034.
 
30 NOVEMBER 4TH TOM HOWARD MYSTERY NOVEL AND SHORT STORY COMPETITION.
Minimum 35,000 words for unpublished mystery novel written in the first
person. Prize for best novel $1,250 cash (incl. advance royalties) plus
publication. Prize for short stories: Three cash prizes: $400, $250 and
$100, incl. fees for once-only publication rights Preference given to
unpublished work. Published novels and stories only considered if author
holds Australian publication rights. For entry forms: 26 Casey Drive, Wyong
NSW 2259.
 
30 NOVEMBER VARUNA FELLOWSHIPS
Writer's retreat fellowships for January June 1996 offer writers in all
genres throughout Australia three weeks of space and time to work
intensively on projects in the Varuna Writers' Centre in the Blue
Mountains. New Writers' Fellowships are available to new writers of any age
and in any medium who are working on a major project but have not yet
received significant publication or performance. Three week Fellowships are
being offered between January and June 1996. Details phone (047) 82 5674.
 
1 DECEMBER MARY GRANT BRUCE STORY COMPETITION
1st prize is $1,000 for a story of up to 3,000 words on an Australian
