Date: Tue, 31 Oct 1995 14:17:45 -0800 (PST)
From: LAURA MORIARTY <moriarty@sfsu.edu>
 
Hi Jordan.
 
Here at the Poetry Center at SF State the rule is once every five years
unless someone wins our book award (a reading is part of the award.) One  thing
I've noticed after helping to run this series
forever is that it can be useful to have a short exchange between the
writers after the reading. If you combine scenes, as Ron suggested, this
can help to make a bridge. We call it a conversation, they more or less
interview each other. A recent one between MichaelPalmer and Norma Cole
produced the question to Michael from Norma: people most often ask me
about you - when did you stop dancing? Of course such an exchange could
degenerate into a fight, but then that would be great. As a final thing,
a sound system can be good, many readings in cafes and bars are just
barely audible.
 
Laura Moriarty
moriarty@sfsu.edu
